WEBVTT

1
00:00:31.298 --> 00:00:35.002
(CAPTAIN PHILLIPS)

2
00:00:41.174 --> 00:00:43.510
(UNDERHILL. VERMONT)

3
00:00:45.178 --> 00:00:48.749
(MARCH 28. 2009)

4
00:00:52.319 --> 00:00:55.222
(MAERSK
LINE. LIMITED)

5
00:01:05.399 --> 00:01:10.170
(Vessel: Maersk Alabama)

6
00:01:36.296 --> 00:01:37.364
Okay.

7
00:01:47.207 --> 00:01:48.208
You all right?

8
00:01:50.010 --> 00:01:51.011
Yeah.

9
00:01:57.150 --> 00:02:00.120
You'd think these trips would get easier
but it's just the opposite.

10
00:02:01.588 --> 00:02:03.390
Well. I feel the same way. Ange.

11
00:02:06.927 --> 00:02:09.096
I know this is what we do.
This is our life.

12
00:02:10.097 --> 00:02:13.900
But it just seems like
the world is moving so fast...

13
00:02:13.900 --> 00:02:18.038
and right now things are changing so much.

14
00:02:20.841 --> 00:02:21.942
They sure are.

15
00:02:24.177 --> 00:02:27.748
I'll tell you something.
It's not gonna be easy for our kids.

16
00:02:28.448 --> 00:02:31.351
They'll be going into a different world
than the one you and I came into.

17
00:02:32.085 --> 00:02:32.953
Yeah.

18
00:02:33.954 --> 00:02:35.789
You know. both our kids are doing great.

19
00:02:36.590 --> 00:02:40.160
But it worries me
when Danny doesn't take school seriously.

20
00:02:41.395 --> 00:02:44.898
Him missing class. That could come out...

21
00:02:44.898 --> 00:02:47.434
it might hurt him when he's out
looking for a job. you know?

22
00:02:48.435 --> 00:02:51.671
The competition out there.
When I was starting out...

23
00:02:51.671 --> 00:02:55.075
you could make captain if you put
your head down and you just did your work.

24
00:02:55.075 --> 00:02:56.543
But young guys coming up now...

25
00:02:57.377 --> 00:02:59.846
companies want things faster and cheaper.

26
00:02:59.846 --> 00:03:01.815
And 50 guys compete for every job.

27
00:03:02.883 --> 00:03:05.152
Everything's different
and big wheels are turning.

28
00:03:05.886 --> 00:03:07.788
You gotta be strong to survive out there.

29
00:03:11.425 --> 00:03:12.659
I hear what you're saying.

30
00:03:13.827 --> 00:03:15.095
It's gonna be okay. right?

31
00:03:16.263 --> 00:03:17.230
Oh. yeah.

32
00:03:20.267 --> 00:03:21.301
Gonna be okay.

33
00:03:32.946 --> 00:03:35.449
"This is a special security announcement."

34
00:03:35.449 --> 00:03:38.518
"Please maintain control
of your personal belongings at all times."

35
00:03:38.518 --> 00:03:42.923
"Unattended baggage is subject
to search. inspection and removal."

36
00:03:48.028 --> 00:03:49.629
- I love you.
- Love you too.

37
00:03:51.164 --> 00:03:53.300
- Have a safe trip.
- I'll call you from there.

38
00:04:06.012 --> 00:04:09.916
(EYL. SOMALIA)

39
00:04:36.776 --> 00:04:37.878
They're here.

40
00:04:39.179 --> 00:04:43.917
Hurry. Muse.

41
00:04:59.966 --> 00:05:02.903
What the hell are you doing?
Why aren't you out on the water?

42
00:05:02.903 --> 00:05:07.707
You know what you're supposed to do.

43
00:05:07.707 --> 00:05:11.411
You should be out there earning money.

44
00:05:11.411 --> 00:05:14.281
But we caught a ship last week.

45
00:05:14.281 --> 00:05:16.650
That was last week.

46
00:05:16.650 --> 00:05:17.817
The boss wants money today.

47
00:05:17.817 --> 00:05:23.223
Bring Garaad another ship soon
or you will answer for it.

48
00:05:23.223 --> 00:05:26.126
Everybody. get back to work now.

49
00:05:36.336 --> 00:05:37.904
Stay out of my way today.

50
00:05:41.408 --> 00:05:43.510
Hufan. Hufan.

51
00:05:44.110 --> 00:05:47.981
I'm going to get us something big.

52
00:05:47.981 --> 00:05:51.551
Those who want to make money. come.

53
00:05:51.551 --> 00:05:53.453
Muse. take me with you.

54
00:05:53.453 --> 00:05:56.756
Does your sister know you're here?

55
00:05:56.756 --> 00:05:58.091
She's selling khat up there.

56
00:05:59.259 --> 00:06:01.428
This is her best stuff.

57
00:06:03.196 --> 00:06:05.131
(SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

58
00:06:07.133 --> 00:06:12.806
When we get a big ship.
you will be well paid.

59
00:06:13.640 --> 00:06:15.108
You want to work?

60
00:06:15.108 --> 00:06:17.510
- Do you know how to steer a boat?
- Yes.

61
00:06:17.510 --> 00:06:18.778
Go. go.

62
00:06:19.913 --> 00:06:21.248
I'm ready.

63
00:06:21.248 --> 00:06:23.049
- What do you have for me?
- Money.

64
00:06:23.049 --> 00:06:25.418
- When are you gonna give it to me?
- As soon as we're paid.

65
00:06:25.418 --> 00:06:27.354
Get on.

66
00:06:27.354 --> 00:06:29.289
Spread out.

67
00:06:29.289 --> 00:06:34.027
Let my other man choose his crew.

68
00:06:34.027 --> 00:06:35.695
- Muse.
- Muse.

69
00:06:35.695 --> 00:06:39.666
Next time bring me something
if you want to work.

70
00:06:47.073 --> 00:06:51.111
(SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

71
00:06:51.111 --> 00:06:53.480
Come on. Bilal.

72
00:06:55.115 --> 00:06:58.652
Hey. Skinny. I can steer your boat.

73
00:06:58.652 --> 00:07:00.120
If you choose me. you won't regret it.

74
00:07:03.790 --> 00:07:04.858
Okay. Elmi.

75
00:07:08.428 --> 00:07:10.096
I need somebody strong.

76
00:07:13.099 --> 00:07:14.668
Somebody like this?

77
00:07:24.311 --> 00:07:26.579
I want him.

78
00:07:27.580 --> 00:07:29.249
Get out of my way.

79
00:07:33.286 --> 00:07:35.155
Why did he pick him?

80
00:07:35.155 --> 00:07:36.856
He's from another village.

81
00:07:54.074 --> 00:07:56.443
(SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

82
00:07:56.743 --> 00:08:00.980
(SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

83
00:08:06.986 --> 00:08:09.656
Move. Move. Move.

84
00:08:27.540 --> 00:08:30.410
Faster. move faster.

85
00:08:30.410 --> 00:08:33.847
(SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

86
00:08:39.386 --> 00:08:41.554
(SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

87
00:08:41.554 --> 00:08:43.089
See if you can get more power.

88
00:08:45.091 --> 00:08:46.993
- Okay.
- You. You.

89
00:08:48.428 --> 00:08:50.463
Get over here.

90
00:08:51.698 --> 00:08:53.066
Come help us.

91
00:09:15.622 --> 00:09:18.825
(SALALAH PORT. OMAN)

92
00:09:56.963 --> 00:09:58.698
Okay. pull it in.

93
00:09:59.966 --> 00:10:01.534
Sign right there. sir.

94
00:10:01.534 --> 00:10:02.702
You have a good day.

95
00:10:03.236 --> 00:10:05.071
- Hello. Cap. Let me get that for you.
- Morning.

96
00:10:58.024 --> 00:11:02.362
"Attention. all crew. All crew.
1500 departure 3 out."

97
00:11:10.837 --> 00:11:13.673
- Hey. good to see you. Cap.
- Shane. Good to see you.

98
00:11:13.673 --> 00:11:16.809
- Good to see you.
- Hey. Carry on.

99
00:11:16.809 --> 00:11:18.211
- Hey. boss?
- Yeah?

100
00:11:18.211 --> 00:11:19.579
Get on that safety rail. huh?

101
00:11:20.346 --> 00:11:21.614
- Kenny.
- Yeah?

102
00:11:21.614 --> 00:11:26.219
I want you to go down to the deck office.
grab Jimmy. get on the Lodestar.

103
00:11:26.219 --> 00:11:28.688
That ballast. move it five points.

104
00:11:29.322 --> 00:11:31.024
- Take care of that now.
- You got it.

105
00:11:32.392 --> 00:11:35.461
- How's the family. Cap?
- Oh. you know.

106
00:11:36.563 --> 00:11:39.966
Andrea's a champ. one kid gone.
another kid going.

107
00:11:40.567 --> 00:11:41.501
How are the boxes?

108
00:11:42.068 --> 00:11:44.370
Oh. you know.
Just putting a few last containers on.

109
00:11:45.071 --> 00:11:49.108
2.400 tons of commercial cargo.
200 tons of food aid...

110
00:11:49.609 --> 00:11:54.948
a 166 tons of freshwater.
250 metric tons of fuel bunkered.

111
00:11:54.948 --> 00:11:56.449
Walk me through the plan.

112
00:11:59.652 --> 00:12:01.688
So here we are in Salalah.

113
00:12:02.655 --> 00:12:04.958
Travel down the coalition corridor
to Djibouti.

114
00:12:05.892 --> 00:12:08.528
Then we exit the shipping lane
south of Socotra.

115
00:12:09.295 --> 00:12:10.630
Socotra. okay.

116
00:12:11.230 --> 00:12:15.034
Then we're on our own down the coast
through the Somali Basin...

117
00:12:15.702 --> 00:12:17.270
all the way down to Mombasa.

118
00:12:18.204 --> 00:12:19.939
"We need five minutes on that reefer bow."

119
00:12:23.509 --> 00:12:26.045
We should be able
to unload the containers around 0800.

120
00:12:28.014 --> 00:12:31.618
Well. let's tighten up security.

121
00:12:31.618 --> 00:12:33.419
We are going around the Horn of Africa.
right?

122
00:12:34.420 --> 00:12:36.889
We got pirate cages. They were all open.

123
00:12:37.624 --> 00:12:38.691
All the doors are unlocked.

124
00:12:38.691 --> 00:12:41.094
I want everything closed. locked.
even in port.

125
00:12:42.662 --> 00:12:46.299
- Right.
- Fine. Ready to leave. 1500.

126
00:12:46.299 --> 00:12:47.734
Absolutely. Cap. You got it.

127
00:12:55.174 --> 00:12:56.275
Stow the gangway.

128
00:12:57.210 --> 00:12:58.478
Last lines in.

129
00:12:59.145 --> 00:13:00.279
Hey. okay.

130
00:13:00.913 --> 00:13:02.181
Okay. Lower it.

131
00:13:02.181 --> 00:13:04.183
Sixteen-B ready. Take it up.

132
00:13:06.719 --> 00:13:07.787
Tighten it up.

133
00:13:08.121 --> 00:13:09.155
Hey. slow down.

134
00:13:10.056 --> 00:13:11.958
(MAERSK ALABAMA
NORFOLK. VA)

135
00:13:13.459 --> 00:13:14.460
Bow clear.

136
00:13:15.228 --> 00:13:16.295
Stern lines are clear.

137
00:13:16.963 --> 00:13:18.297
Bow thruster full starboard.

138
00:13:19.766 --> 00:13:20.933
Bow thruster on.

139
00:13:27.940 --> 00:13:29.876
All lines clear. Ship is under way.

140
00:13:32.111 --> 00:13:34.414
- Dead slow ahead.
- Dead slow ahead.

141
00:13:48.861 --> 00:13:52.832
(MAERSK LINE)

142
00:14:29.969 --> 00:14:32.271
Keep those hatches locked down.

143
00:14:32.271 --> 00:14:33.339
- Cap.
- Morning.

144
00:14:47.453 --> 00:14:48.588
Check that rigging.

145
00:15:02.468 --> 00:15:03.903
- Shane.
- Yeah?

146
00:15:03.903 --> 00:15:05.505
- We need those time sheets.
- Right.

147
00:15:06.706 --> 00:15:09.208
She's winking at me like this.
But it turns out that's what they do.

148
00:15:09.208 --> 00:15:11.911
I'll show you this place.
I'll take you there. We got to go.

149
00:15:11.911 --> 00:15:14.380
I'll have two beers
and a bucketful of sin. please.

150
00:15:16.015 --> 00:15:17.917
Yeah. About done with that coffee?

151
00:15:18.618 --> 00:15:19.519
Right.

152
00:15:20.553 --> 00:15:22.221
- Yeah.
- Yeah. we're done.

153
00:15:23.122 --> 00:15:24.423
That's 15. guys.

154
00:15:25.191 --> 00:15:27.193
Back to work. Come on. let's go.

155
00:15:27.193 --> 00:15:29.362
- Jesus.
- See you down there. Mike.

156
00:15:46.012 --> 00:15:48.214
Their main route is packed with ships...

157
00:15:50.483 --> 00:15:52.952
but we can't attack a herd.

158
00:15:59.292 --> 00:16:01.928
This one is alone.

159
00:16:27.553 --> 00:16:30.056
(PIRACY ALERT WARNING
OFF SOMALI COASTLINE)

160
00:17:00.820 --> 00:17:01.787
Morning.

161
00:17:03.155 --> 00:17:04.090
Hey. Cap.

162
00:17:04.490 --> 00:17:05.458
- Cap.
- Morning. Cap.

163
00:17:06.259 --> 00:17:09.896
Shane. I want to do some security drills.
unannounced.

164
00:17:09.896 --> 00:17:10.997
Starting now.

165
00:17:12.131 --> 00:17:14.233
What? Fire. man overboard?

166
00:17:14.233 --> 00:17:17.103
Everything. Ken. you're the duty officer?

167
00:17:17.103 --> 00:17:18.204
- Yeah. Cap.
- Right.

168
00:17:18.738 --> 00:17:21.274
Boat with two armed men is approaching
on your starboard beam.

169
00:17:23.542 --> 00:17:25.011
- No. no. Whistle first.
- Let's go.

170
00:17:25.311 --> 00:17:28.214
That way the pirates know we're aware
of them and are ready to defend the ship.

171
00:17:30.716 --> 00:17:31.817
Hustle up. Let's go.

172
00:17:34.120 --> 00:17:35.588
Attention. all crew.

173
00:17:35.588 --> 00:17:38.624
"All crew.
All men to your stations on deck."

174
00:17:38.991 --> 00:17:41.661
Repeat. all men to your deck stations now.

175
00:17:42.628 --> 00:17:43.729
Let's do this.

176
00:17:49.035 --> 00:17:50.136
Come on.

177
00:17:50.136 --> 00:17:52.571
Get those keys off your hip.
Put them in your pocket.

178
00:17:52.571 --> 00:17:54.307
Come on. Come on. guys.

179
00:17:54.307 --> 00:17:55.975
Pirates capture you and find those keys...

180
00:17:55.975 --> 00:17:57.977
they'll have access to every door
on this ship.

181
00:18:06.352 --> 00:18:07.787
Get those hoses on.

182
00:18:08.821 --> 00:18:10.356
Bring it around. bring around.
bring around.

183
00:18:11.691 --> 00:18:14.327
- Watch it. man.
- Ready with number six.

184
00:18:14.694 --> 00:18:15.695
All right.

185
00:18:16.329 --> 00:18:17.396
You tied up?

186
00:18:18.130 --> 00:18:19.265
All done here. Shane.

187
00:18:21.100 --> 00:18:24.470
- Hey. Cap. this is Shane. Do you read?
- Yeah. Shane. go ahead.

188
00:18:24.971 --> 00:18:28.874
Things are looking pretty good down here.
We're getting close with the hoses.

189
00:18:28.874 --> 00:18:30.843
All right. Let me know
when you're ready down there.

190
00:18:31.610 --> 00:18:32.645
"Copy that."

191
00:18:52.264 --> 00:18:53.632
Shane. come up to the bridge.

192
00:18:55.201 --> 00:18:56.135
"Okay."

193
00:19:16.288 --> 00:19:17.757
What's up. Cap? Everything okay?

194
00:19:19.191 --> 00:19:20.259
I don't like the look of that.

195
00:19:31.070 --> 00:19:33.472
- Yeah. Cap.
- Chief. I want all your guys on station.

196
00:19:34.974 --> 00:19:37.076
- Still in the drill?
- "No. This is real-world."

197
00:19:37.076 --> 00:19:38.811
We got someone coming up
on our starboard quarter.

198
00:19:39.378 --> 00:19:40.312
Got it.

199
00:19:43.949 --> 00:19:46.018
Port. five degrees.
Let's see if they follow us.

200
00:19:46.986 --> 00:19:48.087
Port. five.

201
00:20:06.505 --> 00:20:08.140
Get the crew back
to their muster stations.

202
00:20:08.707 --> 00:20:09.608
Right.

203
00:20:10.709 --> 00:20:13.746
Attention. all crew. Attention. all crew.
Return to your muster stations.

204
00:20:13.746 --> 00:20:15.815
"Repeat. return to your muster stations."

205
00:20:16.715 --> 00:20:19.452
This is not a drill.
This is a real-world situation.

206
00:20:21.921 --> 00:20:24.557
- Yeah. Cap.
- I want to come up to 122.

207
00:20:24.557 --> 00:20:25.491
Helmsman to the bridge.

208
00:20:25.491 --> 00:20:27.059
Second mate and helmsman to the bridge.
please.

209
00:20:29.228 --> 00:20:30.830
You're good. Bring her on up.

210
00:20:42.074 --> 00:20:43.909
Now get me US Maritime Emergency.

211
00:20:53.085 --> 00:20:55.821
Two skiffs.
Can't tell how many they're carrying.

212
00:20:55.821 --> 00:20:56.956
Copy that.

213
00:20:56.956 --> 00:20:58.991
There's no answer
at the US Maritime Emergency line.

214
00:21:00.092 --> 00:21:02.128
- Raise the UKMTO.
- Right.

215
00:21:02.495 --> 00:21:03.762
What's up?

216
00:21:03.762 --> 00:21:05.798
We got two skiffs approaching.
Get on the radar.

217
00:21:11.070 --> 00:21:13.472
Yeah. this is the Maersk Alabama.
Here's the captain.

218
00:21:15.374 --> 00:21:16.342
UKMTO.

219
00:21:17.710 --> 00:21:19.879
- Operations?
- "Receiving."

220
00:21:19.879 --> 00:21:21.147
This is the Maersk Alabama.

221
00:21:21.147 --> 00:21:26.285
"Our position is 2 degrees 2 north
by 49 degrees 19 east."

222
00:21:26.285 --> 00:21:29.455
"Our course is 180.
Our speed is 17 knots."

223
00:21:29.455 --> 00:21:34.059
We have two skiffs approaching
at a distance of 1.5 miles...

224
00:21:34.059 --> 00:21:36.195
with a possible mothership following.

225
00:21:36.195 --> 00:21:39.031
- "Potential piracy situation."
- Copy. Alabama.

226
00:21:39.031 --> 00:21:41.634
You should alert your crew.
get your fire hoses ready...

227
00:21:41.634 --> 00:21:43.302
and follow lockdown procedures.

228
00:21:45.671 --> 00:21:47.373
Yeah. Is that it?

229
00:21:47.873 --> 00:21:51.577
I'm relaying your transmission now
but chances are it's just fishermen.

230
00:21:51.577 --> 00:21:52.778
They're not here to fish.

231
00:22:13.699 --> 00:22:16.835
She's really big. Get ready.

232
00:22:16.835 --> 00:22:20.272
You worry about yourself. skinny rat.

233
00:22:30.049 --> 00:22:31.650
Both skiffs carrying armed men.

234
00:22:31.917 --> 00:22:34.887
- Distance?
- One and a quarter miles and closing.

235
00:22:39.124 --> 00:22:42.061
- Yeah. Cap.
- I wanna bring it up to 125.

236
00:22:44.597 --> 00:22:46.565
- You're still good.
- 125.

237
00:22:59.144 --> 00:23:04.416
Brothers.
we're going to make a lot of money.

238
00:23:04.416 --> 00:23:06.852
Slow down. The waves are too big.

239
00:23:09.989 --> 00:23:12.725
They're at one mile now. Cap.
Only one mile.

240
00:23:31.410 --> 00:23:33.846
Coalition Warship 237.
this is Maersk Alabama.

241
00:23:33.846 --> 00:23:36.115
Coalition Warship 237. Maersk Alabama.

242
00:23:39.685 --> 00:23:40.786
Go. Alabama.

243
00:23:41.253 --> 00:23:46.191
Our position is 2 degrees 2 north
by 49 degrees 19 east.

244
00:23:46.191 --> 00:23:51.230
"Our course is 180.
Our speed is 18.5 knots."

245
00:23:51.230 --> 00:23:54.700
"We are being approached
by two pirate skiffs..."

246
00:23:54.700 --> 00:23:58.003
"with a possible mothership following."

247
00:23:58.003 --> 00:24:00.372
"We require immediate assistance."

248
00:24:00.939 --> 00:24:02.675
We have a crew of 20.

249
00:24:02.675 --> 00:24:07.479
"We are preparing our weapons now
but request air support if possible."

250
00:24:08.414 --> 00:24:09.415
Copy?

251
00:24:13.552 --> 00:24:16.088
Copy. Alabama.

252
00:24:16.088 --> 00:24:21.327
Be aware. a gunship is in the air.
ETA your position. five minutes.

253
00:24:21.327 --> 00:24:23.595
Five minutes. Thank you. 237.

254
